In most classification tasks, the cross-entropy loss function shown in Eq. (8), is usually the first choice. In our work, aiming to solve the difficulty of cross-entropy loss function on the fuzzy classification boundary, we try to make some modifications on cross-entropy so as to make the classification more effectively. we propose equilibrium cross-entropy by setting MSE as an equilibrium factor of cross-entropy. It can improve the accuracy when the classification boundary is fuzzy.8\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
